PLEASE SHARE! Foster or adoptive home needed in North County San Diego.
“We believe Honey was born in June of 2021. We got her from a lady on Craigslist in on Nov. 16,2021. (The story is a little confusing but here's what we were told)The lady said she rescued Honey and her brother (the only puppies alive out of 5)from a breeder in Colorado who had tied up the mother and left the puppies to die because the mother got impregnated by a rogue dog and they weren't pure bred. She brought the puppies home to Chula Vista and had them vaccinated in Mexico. When we brought Honey to the vet we found she had giardia so we got her treated and cured of that and it was suggested we redo all her vaccinations so we had them redone. She's spayed, microchipped, licensed for 3 yrs along with a 3 yr rabies shot which was done 12/07/22. Shes overdue for  a DHPP Booster (3yr) and a Leptospirosis 4way which I can get done if necessary. She's 50lbs. and gets along with dogs, cats
 and kids. We've lived with her in an apartment (so she is house trained) but she loves to be outside and run around.”
Email 📧 chewslifedogrescue@gmail.com for a foster or adoption application.

Coraline needs a foster in north county San Diego! 

“Coraline will be 3 in October. She is not yet spayed. She is great with other dogs, cats, and kids. She is crate and potty trained. She can be timid at first but then she’ll lay on her back for pets. She loves running with other  dogs and kids. She likes to hang out with the cats but also respect their boundaries. She’s a great cuddler and loves to sleep, cuddle, and sit by people. She’s a smaller mid sized dog and was primarily raised around small dog breeds but she has played with large dog breeds at the beach, during hikes, and at the park.”

Coraline will be spayed by us if someone can foster her. If you’re in north county San Diego and can foster please email 📧 chewslifedogrescue@gmail.com

Driving home tonight I found two puppies wandering on the road and picked them up so the coyotes didn’t get them.
I found out they belong to my neighbor. After speaking with him he said he cannot keep them because his dog had an accidental litter. I took them in and need to find them homes. They are two month old Pittie Husky mixes. One boy the kids named Stevie and a girl named Sunshine. Email me at chewslifedogrescue@gmail.com if you’d like to adopt. I’ll pay for their microchip, vaccinations, and spay and neuter ❤️
